show_title: GM Farcaster ep259 Wednesday June 18, 2025 presented by Octant
text:
Update on Farcaste Pro for developers

1. Farcaster Pro subscription contract is deployed and live on Base. All new subscriptions through the Farcaster app happen onchain (like sign ups). Developers can permissionlessly build on the contract.

2. Contract supports monthly subscriptions. We may add monthly subscriptions and gifting subscriptions to the Farcaster app in the future. Other developers can offer that functionality today if they want.

3. Snapchain is reading from the contract and gating certain features ‚Äî 10K character casts, 4 embeds, profile banners ‚Äî based on pro subscription status.

3. A huge shout out @dynemyte  @blockheim @gabrielayuso.eth @gt @horsefacts.eth @sanjay for all their hard work. From idea to onchain and fully in the protocol in  less than 6 weeks.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep259 Wednesday June 18, 2025 presented by Octant
text:
Lots of mini app related things launching today

- Neynar starter kit is now a deployed mini app so you can see it in action before starting off with it - "npx @neynar/create-farcaster-mini-app" or try linked demo

- starter kit now automatically supports light mode and dark mode switching 

- [this is the big one] there is now a built in Share component that not only allows personalized sharing but automatically tags your _best friends_ on the network so they can try out the app* 

*We calculate best friends for every user and have made this available as an API. This means any mini app developer can now get their users to share their mini app effectively, from the get go!

https://neynar-starter-kit.vercel.app/share/1568

cast.text:
The Neynar Starter Kit  just got some significant updates, making it easier to get started building mini apps for both vibecoders and seasoned devs:

* big facelift for the UI template with tabs and a profile dropdown
* automatic support for dark mode
* built-in share button with the new "best friends API" from @neynar to help users tag the accounts they most interact with when casting a link to your app

Start a new project with "npx @neynar/create-farcaster-mini-app" or try out the live demo below

https://neynar-starter-kit.vercel.app/share/1568

text:
this is how 4 different farcaster clients show my user profile. some interesting notes:

- fc is the only one that hides spam accounts.  of my 9.4k followers, only 3.6k are not ‚Äúspammy‚Äù
- uno shows neither followers or following
- recaster & super display FID
- badges: recaster & super show what i assume to be PRO badges (but might also be power badge remnants). super also shows subscriber badges. no badges on uno. 
- X links on all except uno. fc also shows streaks and $ earned (i deleted it here)
- PFP most prominently displayed on uno, which is a design-forward app. 
- not shown, but super and recaster use your display name (sparkz) in-feed. uno and fc opt for your username (jacy). i have a strong preference for display name over username.
